The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, December 18, 2003 				 Nirvik Singh adjudged best agency head in Asia Pacific
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, Dec. 17: Grey Global group chairman Nirvik Singh has been honoured with the Agency Head of the Year award at MEDIA magazines prestigious Asia Pacific awards in Hong Kong. He is the first Indian to be conferred this honour.																								This award is given to a leader who contributes the most to advance his business and set industry standards. It was fiercely contested by agency heads across the Asia Pacific region. The winner was selected after an exacting judging process conducted by MEDIA, Asias largest magazine for media, marketing and advertising which is published fortnightly from Hong Kong.																								My team and I are delighted by this recognition. Weve spent a couple of years redeploying our talents to yield best practice results across our diverse customer base. It has resulted in gratifying sales and share gains for clients and this award is another acknowledgement that our strategies are paying off, he said. 
